--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
So a piece of leather intrinsically absorbs MORE damage on a warrior (simply because they are a warrior) than on a monk?<br>
Make all the arguements you want about nerfing monks, but don't BS about it.<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Let's get into a fist fight. Put both of us in inch thick padded leather armor. <br>
<br>
I am a 3rd degree black belt. You have no formalized training.<br>
<br>
If you manage to even land a punch on me, I am going to have at the very least partially deflected it. Whereas I am probably going to pound at you, without you having any ability to stop me.<br>
<br>
Armor means a lot, but it doesn't mean everything. So, my point stands.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>EXACTLY</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, you see what you're basically saying there IS that monk should get MORE out of leather armor than a warrior who's used to wearing plate, not <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>less</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
Monks are after all trained to fight in that lighter armor.<br>
Yet the armor itself gives <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>no</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> inherent bonus.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>As far as I can tell, the nerf hit the higher end monks more. Higher end monks get less from their gear than lower end monks do, pound for pound.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Nope it hit those that had their AC well above the new soft caps the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>least</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  This was/is the high level uber monks with more AC than they knew what to do with (the ones that were causing the problems in the first place), and the lower level twinked monks with more AC (for their level) than they knew what to do with.<br>
<br>
The monks that were hit hardest were those that did NOT need to be hit at all. Average mid - high level monks with poor to just above average gear.<br>
<br>
It was a VERY badly implimented nerf.  There are at least 2-3 ways of achieving all the SAME goals without causing all the collateral damage to the class.<br>
<br>
Of course those methods require more work, so I think you can see why VI didn't bother with those options. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>THAT IS HOW IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE. Monks, by all rights, should be below rangers in pure survivability<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->.<br>
<br>
No, VI thinks that monks should deal with damage and tank worse than warriors, pal's, sk's and indeed rangers and BL's.<br>
<br>
However what you've got to remember is that monks are PURE MELEE.  All the really have is their offence/defence ratio.  No spells, no bows, no pets, no real utility.<br>
Currently in situation where FD pulling is not vital that leaves monks as <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">'rogue-lites'</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->.... and that is NOT a viable role. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
So it is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>fine</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to nerf monks mitigation down to the point that warriors, rangers etc. tank better than them, but if you don't then give monks something back you're just breaking monks (much like kunark and rangers).<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Oh come on, you really think wizards and rangers are out-damaging monks? Archery is buggy as hell, and wizard dps sucks no matter how you look at, except on pop boss fights where nobody goes oom. Mages and Monks basically tie even, with rogues far and away above them, and rangers much lower.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
You've obviously not being parsing much.<br>
Once monk gets the really highend equipment and reaches a certain very high level in pure atk their DPS does begin to become viable, but it takes a long time to get there and before that monks are very much subpar (in light of their suddenly aquired subpar defence status) - again this is hurting those who where the target of the nerf the least than those that weren't the most.<br>
<br>
PoP and it's mobs is as much about burst damage as sustained damage, and most of all it's about being able to deal damage with as little risk of taking any in return as possilbe.<br>
<br>
<br>
And lets not forget that nerfing monks did NOT fix warriors (who now still find themselves behind pal &amp; sk's) or fix the problems with the game engine that caused the problems with AC soft caps, mitigation and avoidance etc.  <br>
And certainly did not affect the class envy situation.<br>
<br>
About all it did was mirrior the affects of kunark on rangers (ironically in the very same patch that IMO finally fixed rangers), only this time for monks.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral>General</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
